alerts.title: Flood Advisory
alerts.description: The National Weather Service in New Orleans has issued a * Flood Advisory for... Northwestern Livingston Parish in southeastern Louisiana... South central East Baton Rouge Parish in southeastern Louisiana... * Until 400 PM CDT. * At 259 PM CDT, Doppler radar indicated heavy rain due to thunderstorms. This will cause minor flooding in the advisory area. Up to three inches of rain have already fallen, and an additional inch of rain is possible althrough rainfall rates were decreasing. * Some locations that will experience flooding include... Baton Rouge, Denham Springs, Oak Hills Place, Walker, Westminster, Old Jefferson, Village St. George, Inniswold, Shenandoah and Merrydale.
